9:
Rise up, you women who are at ease, and listen to my voice;
\q1 you carefree daughters, listen to me.
\q1

11:
Tremble, you women who are at ease; be troubled, you confident ones;
\q1 take off your fine clothes and make yourselves bare; put on sackcloth around your waists.
\q1

14:
For the palace will be forsaken, the crowded city will be deserted;
\q1 the hill and the watchtower will become caves forever,
\q1 a joy of wild donkeys, a pasture of flocks;
\q1
